Vermont elected five Democratic-Republicans to the Eighteenth Congress.

Following the 1820 Census, Vermont lost one seat in the House of
Representatives.

Vermont again switched to a statewide at-large system for electing
members to Congress.

In 1824, a [special
election](https://elections.lib.tufts.edu/catalog/tufts:vt.uscongress.special.1824)
was held in which Henry Olin was elected to replace Charles Rich, who
had died.
